== Monster Record Layout ==

Each monster has a 27-byte ($1b) data block starting at Bank 6 $8010:

{| class="wikitable"
! Byte !! Offset !! Name !! Description !! Notes
|-
| 0-1 || +$00 || EXP_Lo/Hi || Experience points (16-bit) || Little-endian
|-
| 2-3 || +$02 || Gold_Lo/Hi || Gold dropped (16-bit) || Little-endian
|-
| 4-5 || +$04 || HP_Lo/Hi || Hit Points (16-bit) || Little-endian, max 65535
|-
| 6 || +$06 || Attack || Attack power || Damage calculation base
|-
| 7 || +$07 || Defense || Defense power || Damage reduction
|-
| 8 || +$08 || Agility || Agility stat || Turn order priority
|-
| 9-14 || +$09 || Skills || 6 bytes of skill/ability data || Action selection pool
|-
| 15-18 || +$0f || Behavior || AI and behavior flags || Pattern control
|-
| 19 || +$13 || Drop_Item || Item drop ID || References item table
|-
| 20 || +$14 || Unknown_20 || Unknown purpose || Usually $00
|-
| 21 || +$15 || Unknown_21 || Unknown purpose || Sprite/palette?
|-
| 22 || +$16 || Metal_Flags || Metal monster flags || Special damage
|-
| 23 || +$17 || Drop_Rate_Flags || Drop rate and additional flags || See below
|-
| 24 || +$18 || Status_Vuln || Status vulnerability flags || Ailment resist
|-
| 25 || +$19 || Unknown_25 || Unknown purpose || TBD
|-
| 26 || +$1a || Unknown_26 || Unknown purpose || TBD
|}

=== Address Formula ===

To find a specific monster's data:
* Monster address = $18010 + (Monster_ID × $1b)
* Example: Monster $05 (Slime) = $18010 + ($05 × $1b) = $18010 + $87 = $18097

== Metal Flags (Byte 22, +$16) ==

Controls special monster types, particularly Metal monsters that take minimal damage.

{| class="wikitable"
! Bits !! Mask !! Description
|-
| 0-1 || $03 || Metal flag ($11 = Metal monster, immune to most damage)
|-
| 2-7 || $fc || Unknown (usually zero)
|}

=== Metal Monster Mechanics ===

When Metal_Flags = $11:
* All non-critical physical attacks deal 0-1 damage
* Spell damage is nullified
* Critical hits deal normal damage
* High flee rate (varies by monster)

